# Problem

the wait() function does not execute properly on the ST Nucleo F411RE board when exported to keil, the wait_ms() function behaves as expected. I believe the function is improperly defined in the port.

for example

``` C
#include "mbed.h"

DigitalOut myled(LED1);
DigitalOut toggle(D7);

int main()
{
    while(1) {
        myled = 0; // LED is OFF
        toggle = 0;
        wait(1);
        myled = 1; // LED is ON
        toggle = 1;
        wait(1); 
    }
}
```
### Online Compiler OK

The above code will behave as expected when compiled online, the led will blink and the toggle will toggle, with 1s intervals.
![capture](https://cloud.githubusercontent.com/assets/5093331/6529466/95f873e2-c3ee-11e4-818b-7a2bec59c472.JPG)
### Offline Compiler problem (keil)

 but when exported to keil the wait function is not behaving properly, the timings are not executing properly with ~2us intervals, which leads me to believe the wait function is entering and immediately exiting. 
![capture2](https://cloud.githubusercontent.com/assets/5093331/6529551/1f208dc6-c3ef-11e4-9bd7-9ef94cfad94e.JPG)
### hotfix

by using wait_us() in keil we can get the expected behavior.
# Acceptance Criteria

the wait() function behaves as expected

